    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-10-16T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-10-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="1600"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1600">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 819.77/83.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Chargé d’Affaires</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 190.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Panama</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-10-16">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 16, 1911</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to my despatch No. 185 of October 10,
                    on the subject of the Panamá-David railway, I have the honor to report that the
                    status of that matter remains the same as before the recent special session of
                    the National Assembly. Both bills passed by this Assembly referring to the
                    financing and construction of that railway have been vetoed by the
                    President.</p>
                <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wm. Whiting Andrews.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
